examples.en: They believed implicitly in their own superiority.
His success has given him a false sense of superiority.
His superiority has woken an ambition in me.
The myth of male superiority was losing its potency.
With the assistance of the bishops they recovered an absolute superiority.
Horace challenges superiority above all the poets.
They disliked his zeal in demonstrating his superiority.
His assurance in his superiority did not make him popular.
He hated the white man's superiority and condescension.
